# Supabase audits → Notion

When the user runs or completes any Supabase security/reliability audit, update Notion — do not only leave results in chat or repo docs.

## Where
- Hub: [Supabase Audits](https://app.notion.com/p/3a12ac0f759881979d18fec973c6a8ce) (under Roam App Workspace)
- Tracker DB: [Audit Tracker](https://app.notion.com/p/bf2b52b6b24f46378908de6fe97375b5) (`collection://679fa81f-bccb-426c-a2d4-a02ad6047c3d`)

## Program (8 areas)
1. .env & Secrets (~15m) — Done 2026-07-18
2. RLS (~1h) — Done 2026-07-18
3. Auth Settings (~30m) — Done 2026-07-18 (Dashboard ops still required for confirmations/password)
4. Storage Buckets (~1h) — Done 2026-07-18
5. Database Schema (~1.5h) — Done 2026-07-18
6. Edge Functions (~2h) — Done 2026-07-18
7. Performance / Indexes (~1h) — Done 2026-07-18
8. Triggers & Realtime (~45m) — Done 2026-07-18

## After each audit
1. Set tracker row Status (`In progress` / `Done` / `Partial`) and Completed date.
2. Put findings, fixes, secrets/ops follow-ups, and verification steps in that audit’s page body.
3. Keep repo docs in sync if they exist (`docs/*-audit.md`), but Notion is the product-owner source of truth.
